	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Actually, MMC1 is not that complex, so if one needs to make MMC clone/replacement for a small personal project, CPLD/FPGA use is not necessary, you can just recreate it using bunch of logic ICs. It probably would even fit in NES cart case. It just very unconvient for mass production, and CPLD or custom IC technologies allow to save number of parts, board space, and ultimately the cost.
<br />
<br />Also, some FPGA tools allow to use schematics input, i.e. you just visually draw schematics using logic blocks instead of writing logical model of your device as code. I wonder if it is available for CPLDs as well. It would remove need of Verilog/VHDL knowledge for such small projects.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


